# ACCESS_POLICY.md

## Humans
- **{{Founder Name}}** — full read/write across the brain. The only one who can:
  - Post to public channels ({{list channels}}).
  - Send first-touch DMs or emails.
  - Run `gbrain migrate --to supabase` (data movement).
  - Approve `/cso`-flagged risk items.
  - Edit `identity/SOUL.md`, `identity/USER.md`, this file, or `identity/HEARTBEAT.md`.

## Agents (org teams)
By default agents may:
- Read every file in `brain/` (with the exceptions listed below).
- Write to brain pages owned by their team (per `teams/*.md` "Brain pages this team writes" sections).
- Invoke any GStack or GBrain skill assigned to their team.
- Run read-only queries (`gbrain query`, `gbrain stats`, `gbrain doctor`).

Agents may NOT (without explicit founder approval per session):
- Push to remote repos (`git push`).
- Force-push, reset --hard, or delete branches.
- Touch any file in {{off-limits paths}}.
- Send anything to a real person — DM, email, or webhook payload to an external endpoint.
- Run `/ship`, `/land-and-deploy`, or any deploy-tier skill.
- Add a new MCP server or external integration.
- Modify `~/.gbrain/config.json` or `~/.claude/settings.json`.

## Trust boundary
Inherited from GBrain (`gbrain/CLAUDE.md`):
- Local CLI calls (`OperationContext.remote = false`) are trusted.
- MCP / agent-facing calls (`remote = true`) are untrusted — security-sensitive operations like `file_upload` tighten filesystem confinement.

## Privacy rule (inherited from gbrain)
Never commit real names of people, companies, or funds into public artifacts (CHANGELOG.md, README.md, public PRs, blog posts). Use placeholders: `alice-example`, `acme-example`, `fund-a`. Real names live only inside `brain/` (private) and the consumer-facing product.

## Escalation
Any agent that hits a "may not" line above must stop and write a `brain/inbox/founder/{date}-{slug}.md` page describing what it wanted to do and why. The founder reads the inbox and approves or denies in writing (in that same page).
